The paper discusses techniques for efficient compensation of frequency selective distortion in unipolar communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), communication systems (cs.COMM), and physical layer communication (cs.PHY). The paper also proposes a new detection scheme, which involves signal processing and noise filtering, making sub-categories such as signal processing (cs.SI) and networked systems (cs.NI) relevant.
